, "id": 8665849, "raw_content": "", "author": "PiratePatriotParrot", "created": 1780865989636, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "WarOfTheFanboys2", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsnFb6vh.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/Polymarket/status/2063689194921435176?s=20", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "JUST IN: The U.S. is reportedly exploring a deal to buy the Chagos Islands from Mauritius, including control of the Diego Garcia military base.", "last_comment_created": 1780932702789, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 157, "score_up": 1003, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 96, "created": 1780856820000, "id": "2063689194921435176", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2005664281002491904/bz2ZO_nU_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Polymarket", "username": "Polymarket"}, "content": "JUST IN: The U.S. is reportedly exploring a deal to buy the Chagos Islands from Mauritius, including control of the Diego Garcia military base.", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 2417}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsnHqo6f", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 31, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8667495, "raw_content": "Article IV, Section 4 of the Constitution. If the elections in California are fraudulent (and it certainly seems like they are), then they are not running a republic, but some sort of oligarchy.\n\n\n\"But what about Article I, Section 4?\"\n\n\nIt's true that it says\n\n\n>The Times, Places and Manner of holding Elections for Senators and Representatives, shall be prescribed in each State by the Legislature thereof; \n\n\nBut it immediately goes on to say\n\n\n>but the Congress may at any time by Law make or alter such Regulations, except as to the Places of chusing Senators.\n\n\nIn other words, the federal gov explicitly has the right to overrule local regulations. All it would take is finding justification from previous acts of congress, possibly even the duty to guarantee a republican form of government, and California (and America) could be saved. \n\n\nDon't know if this will really happen, of course (it should), and I am not a lawyer. I'm just putting the idea out there.", "author": "auroch", "created": 1780933924889, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "auroch", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Re: LA: \"The United States shall guarantee to every State in this Union a Republican Form of Government\"", "last_comment_created": 1780941108192, "content": "<p>Article IV, Section 4 of the Constitution. If the elections in California are fraudulent (and it certainly seems like they are), then they are not running a republic, but some sort of oligarchy.</p>\n<p>&quot;But what about Article I, Section 4?&quot;</p>\n<p>It's true that it says</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The Times, Places and Manner of holding Elections for Senators and Representatives, shall be prescribed in each State by the Legislature thereof;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>But it immediately goes on to say</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>but the Congress may at any time by Law make or alter such Regulations, except as to the Places of chusing Senators.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In other words, the federal gov explicitly has the right to overrule local regulations. All it would take is finding justification from previous acts of congress, possibly even the duty to guarantee a republican form of government, and California (and America) could be saved.</p>\n<p>Don't know if this will really happen, of course (it should), and I am not a lawyer. I'm just putting the idea out there.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 26, "score_up": 31, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}], "status": true}